'''''Miyavi''''' is the eighth studio album by Japanese musician [[Miyavi]]. It was released on June 19, 2013 in Japan, and on March and April 2014 in Europe and United States. It charted as number eight on [[Oricon]] and ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Japan.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/artist/263818/products/music/1021133/1/| title=Miyavi Album on Oricon| publisher=Oricon| accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref><ref name="Billboard Japan">{{cite web| url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=top_albums&year=2013&month=07&day=1| title=Miyavi Album Chart on Billboard Japan| publisher=Billboard Japan| accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref>

== Background ==
The album is Miyavi's eighth studio album, and second since founded his own company J-Glam. The album was released on June 19, 2013 in Japan by [[EMI Records Japan]], and later in March and April 2014 in Europe and United States by [[Wrasse Records]].<ref name="International">{{cite web| url=http://www.en.barks.jp/news/?id=1000004132| title=Miyavi Reveals Cover Art for International Debut Album| date=2014-02-03| work=en.barks.jp| publisher=Global Plus| accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref> It is also available worldwide as a digital release on [[iTunes Store]]. It includes some were previously released singles as well new ones, "Day 1", "Ahead Of The Light" and "Horizon". The music video of "Guard You" was also filmed.<ref name="Guard You">{{cite web| url=http://www.rock-expert.com/video-miyavi-premiering-guard-you-music-video/| title=Miyavi Premiering "Guard You" Music Video| author=Dewa Nugraha| date=2014-03-04| publisher=Rock Expert| accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref> The song was written after the [[2011 Tōhoku earthquake and tsunami|2011 Tōhoku earthquake]], as remembrance of precious people you need to leave behind to guard them.<ref name="Guard You"/> Its video features photos from "Under The Same Sky" project, with scenes of sky and hands by Miyavi's fans.<ref name="Guard You"/>

The limited edition in CD/DVD format, features a bonus DVD with exclusive live footage of "Ahead Of The Light" tour in 2013, and documentary about making the album.

In 2014, Miyavi went on his fourth world tour "Slap the World", which started on February 22 in Malaysia, continued throughout Europe followed by the European release of the latest studio album, and will visit Mexico City and Los Angeles with United States release of the album, before returning to Japan for his longest nationwide tour so far.<ref name="International"/>

== Release ==
When the album was released, it peaked at number eight on the [[Oricon]] and ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' Japan charts in Japan.<ref name="Billboard Japan"/><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/artist/263818/products/music/1021133/1/| title=Miyavi Album chart on Oricon| publisher=Oricon| accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref> It is his second album in top ten, and best selling so far. The singles "Day 1", "Ahead Of The Light" and "Horizon" peaked on [[Japan Hot 100]] at number sixty-six,<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=hot100&year=2012&month=07&day=23| title=Day 1 chart on Hot 100 of Billboard Japan| publisher=Billboard Japan| accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref>  twenty-one<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=hot100&year=2013&month=03&day=04| title=Ahead Of The Light chart on Hot 100 of Billboard Japan| publisher=Billboard Japan| accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref> and forty-nine.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=hot100&year=2013&month=07&day=1| title=Horizon chart on Hot 100 of Billboard Japan| publisher=Billboard Japan| accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref> They also charted on Hot 100 Airplay, as number sixty-three,<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=top_airplay&year=2012&month=07&day=30| title=Day 1 chart on Hot 100 Airplay of Billboard Japan| publisher=Billboard Japan| accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref> twenty-one,<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=top_airplay&year=2013&month=03&day=4| title=Ahead Of The Light chart on Hot 100 Airplay of Billboard Japan| publisher=Billboard Japan| accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref> and thirty-six.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=top_airplay&year=2013&month=07&day=1| title=Horizon chart on Hot 100 Airplay of Billboard Japan| publisher=Billboard Japan| accessdate=May 2, 2014| deadurl=yes| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131214075711/http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=top_airplay&year=2013&month=07&day=1| archivedate=December 14, 2013| df=}}</ref> "Horizon" also charted as thirty-nine on Adult Contemporary list.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=adult_airplay&year=2013&month=07&day=01| title=Horizon chart on Adult Contemporary of Billboard Japan| publisher=Billboard Japan| accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref>

In 2013, Miyavi and [[Yuksek]] received the Best Collaboration award for "Day 1" at the [[2013 MTV Video Music Awards Japan|MTV Video Music Awards Japan]], and in 2014 the music video of "Horizon" was nominated for the Best Male Video category.

